star.idres.lookup

Interface ReportingSystemLookup<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type that is used to represent the identifier that is transmitted in the messages of the reporting system
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AISLookup, LRITLookup, VMSLookup

    public interface ReportingSystemLookup<T>
    A generic interface that defines the common methods used to retrieve the mapping between the transmitted identifiers and the surrogate identifiers.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getVesselID

        Optional<VesselID> getVesselID(T transmittedId,
                               Date timestamp)
        Returns the VesselID for the vessel that is known to have been transmitting the specified identifier at a certain point in time.
        Parameters:
        transmittedId - the identifier transmitted from the vessel
        timestamp - the time when the message was transmitted
        Returns:
        the reference to the vessel that the transmission is supposed to come from or an empty value if the vessel is not known

      • getTransmittedIDs

        Collection<TemporalValue<T>> getTransmittedIDs(VesselID vesselId,
                                               com.google.common.collect.Range<Date> period)
        Returns a collection of identifiers that were transmitted by the specific vessel during the requested period. Note that in most cases the result will contain a single value. The possibility to return multiple values is only necessary to cover the case when the vessel has changed its transmitted identifier during the requested period. The result also contains the time period during which the given identifier was transmitted.
        Parameters:
        vesselId - the vessel whose transmitted identifiers are requested
        period - the time period during which the vessel was transmitting the returned identifiers
        Returns:
        a collection of identifiers associated with the time period during which the vessel was transmitting them
